The key elements of the NAP process include:
* Building appropriate capacity for adaptation action;
* Defining adaptation options at the various levels of governance;
* Creating an enabling environment for effective adaptation;
* Designing a coherent approach to fund mobilization for effective climate change
* Developing suitable strategies for engaging the private sector;
* Developing effective communication strategies in the various phases of the adaptation
* Developing an effective monitoring and evaluation plan to facilitate implementation.
